# TestRail draft > ACC (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

For **new cases from a story**, follow **`testrail-case-generate.mdc`** in full (Learn > Plan > Draft > batch of 5 > ACC all > then write).

## Absolute ban

Until the user explicitly replies **ACC**, **APPROVE**, **ACC all** (per batch), or equivalent for that draft set:

- **FORBIDDEN:** `addCase`, `updateCase`, `addSection`, `updateSection`, `deleteCase`, `deleteSection`
- **FORBIDDEN:** Shortcut `stories-add-task` for new qa-test checklists of cases not yet approved
- **FORBIDDEN:** writing cases immediately because the story looks Done or AC is clear

**Violation = hard stop.** Draft only. Wait.

## Required draft fields (every case)

| Field | Required |
|-------|----------|
| **Title** | Yes - `When …, then …` · `[neg]` if negative |
| **Test case objective** | Yes |
| **Precondition** | Yes |
| **Test step** | Yes |
| **Test expectation** | Yes |
| **Test data** | Yes if any values used. Else `N/A` |

## Delivery (summary)

1. Learn from Shortcut. Unclear → ask or Glean. Never invent.
2. Show **plan** (titles only). Wait ACC plan / EDIT plan.
3. Draft fields. Preview file complete under `generated-tests/manual/`.
4. Chat: **max 5 cases** per turn. Wait ACC / EDIT / REJECT / DELETE before next batch.
5. Only after **all** surviving cases ACC'd → `addCase` + checklist.
6. Case **update** / plan / results: same ACC gate (methodology Phase 7 + case maintenance).

## Titles / checklist after ACC

`testrail-case-titles.mdc` · `testrail-shortcut-checklist.mdc`
